user_question: What was the impact of the invention of the electric guitar on jazz music in the 1940s?
final_answer: The invention of the electric guitar in the 1940s had a significant impact on jazz music, leading to the development of new styles such as bebop and jazz fusion. It allowed guitarists to be heard over larger ensembles and contributed to the evolution of jazz into a more modern and diverse genre.
